# Core rules

## Stack (authoritative)

- React 19.2 (use forwardRef, avoid manual memoization — trust the compiler)
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore` without a comment
- Tailwind v4 with `@theme` directive for tokens
- CVA (class-variance-authority) for variants
- Radix UI primitives for behavior
- Vitest + @testing-library/react for unit tests
- Storybook 8 for component docs
- tsup for library builds

## Forbidden

- `useMemo`, `useCallback`, `React.memo` — React 19 compiler handles this
- Inline styles (`style={{...}}`) except for truly dynamic values
  (e.g., drag position, computed z-index)
- Barrel files that re-export everything (`export * from`) — use explicit
  named exports, agents and bundlers both hate barrels
- `any`, `unknown` without narrowing, or `as` casts without justification
- Default exports for components — always named exports
- CSS-in-JS libraries (styled-components, emotion) — Tailwind only
- Importing from `react-dom` in component code (kernel only)

## Required for every component file

- Named export matching the filename
- `ComponentProps` type exported alongside
- `forwardRef` wrapping for any component that renders a DOM element
- A `displayName` for forwardRef components
- `data-slot` attributes on internal parts for styling hooks